                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate all shouts before combat</strong> &mdash; War Cry, Rallying Cry, and Challenging Shout. This gives you full offensive and defensive buffs before engaging packs.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Hold down Whirlwind and spin through enemies</strong> &mdash; Your primary action. Hold the button and guide your character through packs, dealing constant AoE damage to everything in range.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Dust Devils spawn automatically</strong> &mdash; Thanks to Grasping Whirlwind gloves, tornadoes spawn as you spin. These provide persistent damage zones that continue hitting enemies after you pass through.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Recast shouts on cooldown</strong> &mdash; Keep War Cry, Rallying Cry, and Challenging Shout up at all times. Rage of Harrogath reduces their cooldowns for near-permanent uptime.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Pop Wrath of the Berserker for burst windows</strong> &mdash; Use your Ultimate during high-density packs, dangerous elite encounters, or when you need the Unstoppable to break CC and survive.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Use Lunging Strike only when Fury is critically low</strong> &mdash; If you run out of Fury in low-density areas, use Lunging Strike a few times to generate resource before spinning again.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Stop spinning near elites for Gohr's explosion</strong> &mdash; Whirlwind explodes when it ends thanks to Gohr's Devastating Grips. Stop spinning near priority targets to trigger the explosion for burst damage.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
